One important point I scrutinized is the interaction with boot parameters. The code includes a check (`!ctx`) to prevent a null pointer dereference during early boot. Returning `-EBUSY` when `commit_inputs=Y` is provided as a boot parameter is an intended behavior change and can potentially break scripts that incorrectly try to commit during module load. However, this is an acceptable API change as the parameter should only be used after module loading.

